    "objective": "“to estimate individual patients’ Km and Vm values and then to compare them to published literature values”",
    "covariates": "Tested: - Included: WT on Vm",
    "observations": "One dose-concentration pair was sufficient to estimate individual kinetic parameters Vm and Km. The authors fail to provide an exhaustive comparison of their parameter values to those in literature. Vm (as mg/day/kg) is poorly correlated against weight, as would be expected given that Vm is already corrected for weight. In fact, the negative correlation found could be explained by the nonlinear correlation (usually Vm=theta*((WT/WTm)**0.75)) being forced into a linear one.",
    "dose": "Steady-state oral doses in patients",
    "structure": "Undocumented",
    "equations": "Km=theta1*(1+eta1) Vm=theta2*WT*(1+eta2) Css=(Km*DD)/(Vm-DD)",
    "parameter_values": "theta1=3.66 theta2=7.29 omega1=0.044 omega2=0.028",
    "validation": "No/No"
  },
